.TH "tty_buffer_space_avail" 9 "tty_buffer_space_avail" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tty_buffer_space_avail \- return unused buffer space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tty_buffer_space_avail
.BI "(struct tty_port *port "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
tty port owning the flip buffer

Returns the # of bytes which can be written by the driver without
reaching the buffer limit.
.SH "NOTE"
this does not guarantee that memory is available to write
the returned # of bytes (use \fBtty_prepare_flip_string_xxx\fP to
pre-allocate if memory guarantee is required).
